{
  "texts": [
    "Velocity just quantifies the speed of writing and abnormal variability in writing speed is related to the underlying handwriting problems.",
    "Acceleration computes the variability in the velocity during writing.",
    "Jerk is the change in acceleration over time per stroke.",
    "Unusual Fig. 7 Relevant handwriting features changes in acceleration over time per stroke may be related to writing problems.",
    "Various studies [47,48] in the literature have found that the kinematic aspects are affected in children with handwriting disabilities."
  ]
}